{"action": "input", "code": "def enlarge_grid(grid1: np.ndarray, h: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    h1, w1 = grid1.shape\n    w2 = int(w1 * h / h1)\n    return np.repeat(np.repeat(grid1, h, axis=0), w2, axis=1)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    h, w = get_height_and_width(input_grid)\n    grid1, grid2 = divide_image(input_grid)\n    large_gird = enlarge_grid(grid1, h)\n    output_grid = merge_grids(large_grid, h, grid2)\n    return output_grid\ndef divide_image(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    h, w = get_height_and_width(input_grid)\n    if h < w:\n        mid = w // 2\n        left_half = input_grid[:, :mid]\n        right_half = input_grid[:, mid:]\n        return (left_half, right_half)\n    else:\n        mid = h // 2\n        upper_half = input_grid[:mid, :]\n        lower_half = input_grid[mid:, :]\n        return (upper_half, lower_half)\ndef get_height_and_width(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = input_grid.shape\n    return (h, w)\ndef merge_grids(large_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, small_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    h1, w1 = large_grid.shape\n    h2, w2 = small_grid.shape\n    x = int((w1 - w2) / 2)\n    y = int((h - h2) / 2)\n    large_grid[y:y + h2, x:x + w2] = small_grid\n    return large_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Task description: \n    # The input is a rectangular image matrix with a black background (the black part is considered a hole), and the width of the image is twice the length. Here are the steps you need to take:\n    # Step 1: Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w.\n    # Step 2: If h <w, divide the image matrix into left and right halves, else if h>w, divide the image matrix into up and down halves, denoted as grid1 and grid2 (both are squares with a size of h*h).\n    # Step 3: Enlarge grid1 proportionally by h times, denoted as large_grid (the size of large_grid is h^2*h^2).\n    # Step 4: Traverse in large_grid according to the size of h*h (large_grid can be divided into h^2 h*h squares, with h squares horizontally and vertically).\n    #   (4-1) Get the color of the current h*h square, denoted as c;\n    #   (4-2) If the color of the current h*h square is not black, replace it with grid2.\n    #   (4-3) Paint the non-empty part of the current h*h square with color c.\n    (h, w) = `Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w.`(input_grid)\n    (grid1, grid2) = `If h <w, divide the image matrix into left and right halves, else if h>w, divide the image matrix into up and down halves (both are squares with a size of h*h).`(input_grid)\n    large_gird = `Enlarging grid1 proportionally by h times.`(grid1, h)\n    output_grid = `Execute Step4 in the task description.`(large_grid, h, grid2)\n    return output_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def enlarge_grid(grid1: np.ndarray, h: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    h1, w1 = grid1.shape\n    w2 = int(w1 * h / h1)\n    return np.repeat(np.repeat(grid1, h, axis=0), w2, axis=1)\ndef divide_image(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    h, w = get_height_and_width(input_grid)\n    if h < w:\n        mid = w // 2\n        left_half = input_grid[:, :mid]\n        right_half = input_grid[:, mid:]\n        return (left_half, right_half)\n    else:\n        mid = h // 2\n        upper_half = input_grid[:mid, :]\n        lower_half = input_grid[mid:, :]\n        return (upper_half, lower_half)\ndef get_height_and_width(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = input_grid.shape\n    return (h, w)\ndef merge_grids(large_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, small_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    h1, w1 = large_grid.shape\n    h2, w2 = small_grid.shape\n    x = int((w1 - w2) / 2)\n    y = int((h - h2) / 2)\n    large_grid[y:y + h2, x:x + w2] = small_grid\n    return large_grid", "holes": {"enlarge_grid": "Enlarging grid1 proportionally by h times.", "divide_image": "If h <w, divide the image matrix into left and right halves, else if h>w, divide the image matrix into up and down halves (both are squares with a size of h*h).", "get_height_and_width": "Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w.", "merge_grids": "Execute Step4 in the task description."}}
